ical-confirmation/4019364.article">The nuances of chemical confirmation</a></h2><p class="meta"><span class="author">By <a rel="author" href="https://www.chemistryworld.com/vanessa-seifert/500159.bio">Vanessa Seifert</a></span></p><p class="intro">Supporting a hypothesis is more difficult than it might seem<strong></strong></p></div></div></div><div class="spinLayout full twocol left item-third item-penultimate"><div class="sleeve"><p class="picture"><a href="https://www.chemistryworld.com/opinion/letters-may-2024/4019360.article" class="image"><img alt="Fountain pen nib, writing" class="lazyloaded" loading="lazy" src="https://d2cbg94ubxgsnp.cloudfront.net/Pictures/460x307/9/3/3/533933_shutterstock_286104224.jpg" srcset="https://d2cbg94ubxgsnp.cloudfront.net/Pictures/460x307/9/3/3/533933_shutterstock_286104224.jpg 460w" width="460" height="307" /></a></p><div class="subSleeve"><h2><a href="https://www.chemistryworld.com/opinion/letters-may-2024/4019360.article">Letters: May 2024</a></h2><p class="meta"><span class="author">By <a rel="author" href="https://www.chemistryworld.com/chemistry-world/1210.bio">Chemistry World</a></span></p><p class="intro">Readers call for cross-industry support, celebrate variety and debate the evidence for Z-DNA’s handedness&nbsp;</p></div></div></div><div class="spinLayout full twocol right item-fourth item-last"><div class="sleeve"><p class="picture"><a href="https://www.chemistryworld.com/opinion/lab-automation-gives-me-more-time-at-the-top-of-the-mountain/4019370.article" class="image"><img alt="A hiker stands at the top of a mountain looking down over clouds and a sunset" class="lazyloaded" loading="lazy" src="https://d2cbg94ubxgsnp.cloudfront.net/Pictures/460x307/8/9/1/533891_gettyimages1324403872_34607_crop.jpg" srcset="https://d2cbg94ubxgsnp.cloudfront.net/Pictures/460x307/8/9/1/533891_gettyimages1324403872_34607_crop.jpg 460w" width="460" height="307" /></a></p><div class="subSleeve"><h2><a href="https://www.chemistryworld.com/opinion/lab-automation-gives-me-more-time-at-the-top-of-the-mountain/4019370.article">Lab automation gives me more time at the top of the mountain</a></h2><p class="meta"><span class="author">By <a rel="author" href="https://www.chemistryworld.com/derek-lowe/1294.bio">Derek Lowe</a></span></p><p class="intro">Getting back to the bench reminds Derek Lowe how much has changed in 40 years</p></div></div></div></div></div></div>
